st\">\n<li>Grass-fed beef tallow (base)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Beeswax (adds structure and protection)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Raw honey or herbal infusions (optional soothing boost)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Occasionally, olive oil or jojoba oil for glide</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Who It’s Best For</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>People with <strong>very dry or sensitive skin</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Those reacting to conventional creams</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Minimalist/natural skincare users</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cold climate or harsh weather exposure</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Anyone wanting a <strong>multi-use</strong> balm instead of multiple products</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Use</h2>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Take a <strong>pea-sized</strong> amount.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Warm between fingertips until it melts.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Press gently into slightly damp skin (best after washing).</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Use once or twice daily.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A little goes a long way.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Things to Know</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Natural, mild scent (no added fragrance)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Firmer at room temp; melts on contact</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Best stored away from heat</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shelf-stable due to low water content</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">In essence</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A tallow moisturizer is a <strong>traditional, nutrient-rich skin balm</strong> that prioritizes barrier health, deep hydration, and ingredient simplicity—making it especially effective for dry, sensitive, or compromised skin.</p>\n"
